  "body": "<!--\r\nIf you are reporting a new issue, make sure that we do not have any duplicates\r\nalready open. You can ensure this by searching the issue list for this\r\nrepository. If there is a duplicate, please close your issue and add a comment\r\nto the existing issue instead.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Description**\r\nNamespace validation is oddly specific. The following pops up in error logs\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror=\"namespace validation: namespace \\\"space47-9a\\\" must match ^[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9]+(:?[-]+[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9]+)*(?:[.](?:[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9]+(:?[-]+[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9]+)*))*$: invalid argument\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo this means that `space47-a9` is legit, but `space47-9a` is somehow not? Same thing for periods, they must be followed by an alpha and then alphanumerics. is there are reason behind this? What is wrong with following a hyphen with a number?\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the issue:**\r\n1. create a namespace with a hyphen followed by a number\r\n\r\n**Describe the results you received:**\r\nNamespace creation failed\r\n\r\n**Describe the results you expected:**\r\nNamespace creation succeeded\r\n\r\n**Output of `containerd --version`:**\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontainerd github.com/containerd/containerd v1.2.2 9754871865f7fe2f4e74d43e2fc7ccd237edcbce\r\n```",
